Are We Being Bad Citizens If We Don't Keep Up With the News?

In your opinion, are we being bad citizens if we don't keep up with the news? Do you think all people have some responsibility to know what is going on in the world? Does engaging with current events actually do anything at all? Why do you think the way you do?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We should focus on our families, friends, and communities.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We should focus on our own personal growth.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: But, if you're reading it every day, you're wasting your time.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We should focus on our own lives, and not worry about what the Kardashians are doing.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It's not our fault that these things happen, and we can't do anything about it.

actions.text: We can volunteer at our local schools.
